Open Source Data Science Platform

Kontarion is a containerized Data Science platform with support for GPU accelerated AI / ML based on “Rocker project” stacks extended w Python/Anaconda and more.

Supports polyglot data science workflows:

  • R with web UI (RStudio) and with Shiny, RStudio and Rmarkdown Notebooks.
  • Python with Jupyter Notebooks.
  • Supports also other languages used in Data Science (STAN, C, C++ etc)

Moby, Docker? Deploy it where containers run!

Container Contents

Base stack from ROpenSci - starts from a versioned “Rocker project” stack for machine learning and adds Anaconda/Python/Jupyter and more.

  • Containers are on Docker Hub at https://hub.docker.com/r/kthb/kontarion (“docker pull kthb/kontarion”)
  • Sources are on GitHub on https://github.com/KTH-Library/kontarion
  • Demo/use case example: Bibliometrics at KTH - Royal Institute of Technology: https://kth-library.github.io/

Annual Bibliometric Monitoring @ KTH

Benefits

Traditional Business Intelligence software doesn’t have a great fit with modern agile data science workflows on the web. In comparison, Kontarion offers:

  • Less vendor lock-in (and open source licensing reduces cost).
  • An open source based platform making use of containers
  • Support data science work with R and Python for ML/AI, including GitHub/DockerHub-friendly workflows.
  • Support ML/AI w GPU acceleration for Big Data / Fast Data (connects to Apache Spark)
  • Support developing and deployment of APIs, Web apps and other data infrastructure components

Use cases and contact

Use cases

Although currently used primarily for Bibliometric analytics @ KTH, other data science workflows are supported:

  • https://spark.rstudio.com/mlib/ (Spark Machine Learning lib!)
  • https://blogs.rstudio.com/tensorflow/
  • https://tensorflow.rstudio.com/
  • https://www.r-bloggers.com/
  • https://plot.ly/dash/
  • https://shiny.rstudio.com/

Runs where containers run (deploy with Docker Swarm / Kubernetes etc).
